statement_latex:
Find the least nonnegative integer x that satisfies the following system
of linear congruences.

\begin{align*}
x &\equiv 998 \mod{999}\\
x &\equiv 999 \mod{1000}\\
x &\equiv 1000 \mod{1001}
\end{align*}

statement_raw:
Find the least nonnegative integer x that satisfies the following system of linear congruences.

&lt;math> \displaystyle 
\begin{align}
x &amp;\equiv 998 \mod{999}\\
x &amp;\equiv 999 \mod{1000}\\
x &amp;\equiv 1000 \mod{1001}
\end{align}
&lt;/math>
